The version numbers I recall (strictly from fallible memory alone) are:
1.91, 2.19, 3.27, 4S50, and 4S72; all pre-Level D. 

Disk/file handling was changed significantly with the introduction of Level-D 
disk service, released with the first 5 series monitor. In its first 
incarnation the Level-D file service routine was one module called FILSER. It 
was written by Tony Wachs from design work by Tony, Chris White, and Tom 
Hastings. It was about this time monitor source editing conventions were also 
introduced as documented in a memo called LEVELD.MEM, written by Tom 
Hastings.

As I recall, the first 5 series release still preserved the old, 
non-standardized AC namings; eg. PDP, TAC, TEMP, etc. These were codified and 
changed by Don Black for the same release that introduced the FILSER split 
into FILIO, FILUUO, and FILINT (I think those were the names), and for which 
I implemented extended RIBs. This was either 5.01 or 5.02, I'm leaning toward 
5.01.

So which drastic change were you referring to?





