>implementation.  First KS monitor.  Last KA monitor.  User mode access 
control
>lists (FILDAE).  That sort of stuff.

Most of the above were evolutionary changes introduced over a period of 
years. PPNs (project, programmer numbers) were already in place in the PDP-6 
monitor in the mid-60s. SFDs (sub-file directories) appeared in an early 5 
series release (I think) like 5.01 or 5.02. I don't recall the sequence of 
memory management changes leading from the KA's shuffler to demand paging, 
but I do recall implementing DAEMON enhancements to DCORE and DUMP required 
to support demand paging. This was in 1973-74 or so. I believe this was for 
the first KL implementation but I forget the version number. First KS monitor 
was 1978. I know this one because I ported TOPS-10 to the KS. I almost got 
caught in the great blizzard of '78; I stayed late in Marlboro after DEC had 
sent everybody home so I could get stand-alone time on the development KS. I 
barely made it home.

So "that sort of stuff" actually appeared over a period of 10+ years.

